Before any significant workload: read docs/kb/agent-delegation.md to determine how to break down the task


## Model selection

| Type | Rule |
|------|------|
| Custom (`task-executor`, `critical-reviewer`) | Do not pass `model`; defined in agent files. |
| Built-in (`explore`, `shell`, `generalPurpose`) | Always `model: "fast"` unless: prior fast attempt failed OR task requires architectural judgment OR requirements are ambiguous and need interpretation. |

## Subagent type selection

| Task | Type |
|------|------|
| Quick reads / searches | `explore` |
| Running shell commands | `shell` |
| 1–2 file edits | `generalPurpose` |
| Multi-file implementation | `task-executor` |
| Code review / audits | `critical-reviewer` |
| ≥10 files across ≥2 modules with dependencies, or ≥4 coordinated task-executor calls | `task-orchestrator` |

## Task orchestrator (multi-layer delegation)

Use `task-orchestrator` when scale or coordination thresholds are met (see table above). The orchestrator owns explore → execute → review within a bounded scope; top-level orchestrator reviews the report and owns overall direction.